The governorship candidate of Abia State of the All Progressives Grand Alliance (APGA) in Abia State, Dr. Alex Otti has vowed to unseat Dr. Okezie Ikpeazu’s PDP-led government. In a statement issued by his Media and Publicity Director, Mr. Kazie Uko, Otti accused Ikpeazu of lack of love for Abians and incapable of bringing meaningful development to the people.Otti, who is challenging Ikpeazu’s election at the Election Tribunal urged the tribunal to declare the state 2019 gubernatorial poll as inconclusive and order a repeat poll in 788 units across the state. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .